 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-BOUNDARY: Observation-driven boundary measurement for external projects. CONTEXT: DOGFOOD-2 Agent C did a spec-impl audit and saw 'boundaries: spec-impl (not measured)' on every status check — while literally auditing spec-impl alignment. Bilateral value scored 5/10. RATIONALE: When an agent observes 'APP-INV-071 DIVERGENT' or 'APP-INV-001 ALIGNED', that IS boundary measurement data. The boundary should update. APPROACH: (1) In bilateral.rs or a new external_boundary module, add observation_boundary_signal(store) -> Option<BoundaryMetric>. (2) Scan session observations for patterns: 'aligned', 'divergent', 'missing', 'conformant', 'violated', 'passes', 'fails' + spec ID patterns (APP-INV-NNN, INV-*, ADR-*). (3) Count aligned vs divergent observations. Compute ratio: boundary_score = aligned_count / (aligned_count + divergent_count). (4) If at least 2 observations mention spec alignment, report as boundary metric in braid status: 'boundaries: observation-based N/M (N aligned, M-N divergent)'. (5) This is lightweight — no bilateral scan needed, just observation text parsing. It activates the boundary reporting that was inert on external projects. (6) Wire into F(S): observation-based boundary contributes to the coherence component, making F(S) responsive to audit work. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After Agent C's 5 observations (3 aligned, 1 partial, 1 divergent): boundary shows '3/5 (60%)'. (B) With zero alignment observations: boundary shows '(not measured)' (no change). (C) F(S) changes when alignment observations are recorded. (D) Works on any project with any spec format (C8). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs"
